# Backend Rules - planning-poker-jira-service

## Scope

`planning-poker-jira-service` owns Jira Cloud REST access, scope search/enrichment, changelog/status milestone parsing, role contributors and optional GitLab evidence.

It is stateless: no Postgres, Redis, sessions, RBAC or scope-board persistence.

## Read Before Changing

- Service boundaries: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/architecture/SERVICES.md`.
- Jira contract: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/contracts/JIRA-SERVICE.md`.
- Scope board contract: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/contracts/SCOPE-BOARD.md`.
- Development practices: `../planning-poker-dev/docs/development/GUIDE.md`.

## Implementation Rules

- Keep Jira adapter contracts stable unless the task explicitly requires a contract change.
- Preserve singleton client/cache behavior; do not create per-request Jira clients for readiness or normal requests.
- Keep Jira/GitLab HTTP concerns in adapters; keep parsing/enrichment logic in domain/utils where existing patterns place it.
- Do not add persistence, RBAC/session logic or frontend assumptions to this service.
- Sanitize external data before returning it to callers.
- Do not log Jira tokens, credentials, request auth headers or sensitive issue data beyond existing safe context.

## Testing

- Changed parsing/enrichment/API logic requires pytest coverage in `tests/`.
- Contract changes require tests for response shape and error behavior.
- Retry/rate-limit/dependency-failure behavior needs regression coverage when touched.
- Run `python3 -m pytest -q` before commit/push.

## Documentation

Update `../planning-poker-dev/docs/contracts/JIRA-SERVICE.md` or related docs when endpoints, response shapes, config or integration behavior changes.
